Here you will find every commands about Docker!

docker --help ~> Show help about Docker
docker --version ~> Show version of Docker
docker --license ~> Show license of Docker

docker image list ~> List all images
docker image pull python ~> Pull image from DockerHub
docker image inspect python ~> Inspect image
docker container run <params> <image> <CMD> <arguments> ~> Run container
docker container run -d <params> <image> <CMD> <arguments> ~> Run container in background
docker container stop <container> ~> Stop container

-i ~> Interactive mode
-t ~> Interactive mode with tty
-d ~> Detached mode
-p <port> ~> Port to expose
-v <volume> ~> Volume to expose
-m <memory> ~> Limit the RAM Memory
-c <cpu> ~> Limit the CPU

docker ps ~> List all containers
docker container run -it --rm -p 80:8080 python ~> Run container with port 8080

==================================================================================

docker container list <parÃ¢metros> ~> List all containers
-a ~> List all containers (including stopped containers)
-l ~> List the last containers (including offline containers)
-q ~> Only display the containers IDs

==================================================================================

docker container start <container> ~> Start container
docker container stop <container> ~> Stop container
